These run script templates are dedicated to code for generating the Hamiltonian for a {p, 3} hyperbolic lattice
with external uniform magnetic field (parameterized by beta, see below) and obtaining the DOS of the Hamiltonian
from utilization of the kernal polynomial method (KPM).

General conventions:
pval and qval are the {p, q} appearing in the Schlafli symbol for hyperbolic lattices
nval is the number of generations (unlike paper in code we start counting from 1 not 0)
alpha_NH is the alpha appearing in the NH construction, controlling the strength of the NH
Nm is the number of moments to compute in the Chebyshev polynomial expansion in KPM

Note that since KPM requires rescaling of the Hamiltonian, bounds of the eigenspectrum must be given.
Exact bounds could be computed via Lanczos algorithm, however it is more efficient to statically set these
bounds here since the eigenspectrum of all q=3 lattices should safely fall in the range [-3.12, 3.12],
hence the bounds set in the run template.
